people throw the word monopoly around today, but they don't really understand it. Historical monopolies have not only had the vast majority of market share in their primary market, but they used it to get market share and control other markets.

&amp;#x200B;

The oil trust captured the majority of market share in drilling, refining and sales. and I forgot what else they had control of. AT&amp;T controlled over 90% of the local and long distance and phone markets until the 80's and locked out DSL, fax and other disruptive tech for years. When I had Ma Bell service we had to walk like 2 miles to the store and buy or rent their phone and no other phones were available or would work. not like today.

&amp;#x200B;

apple, amazon and Facebook aren't monopolies by the historical definition . MS had over 90% of the desktop OS market and used it to capture majority shares in the server OS, applications and office applications and was kind of a monopoly. but by the time the court cases finished they were losing their control and so it was unlike historical monopolies.

